1
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:24,483
[dramatic music]

2
00:00:26,142 --> 00:00:28,338
So you're sure
you'll be all right?

3
00:00:28,377 --> 00:00:30,312
- What, Basil?
- You'll be all right?

4
00:00:30,346 --> 00:00:32,815
Will you get me my bed jacket?

5
00:00:32,848 --> 00:00:34,043
Bed jacket.

6
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:35,483
In the drawer, the blue one,

7
00:00:35,518 --> 00:00:36,816
in the drawer!

8
00:00:38,788 --> 00:00:41,314
Now, you won't forget
the fire drill tomorrow?

9
00:00:41,357 --> 00:00:43,326
I won't, dear. I can
cope, you know.

10
00:00:43,359 --> 00:00:44,588
This one?

11
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:45,822
That's not blue.

12
00:00:45,861 --> 00:00:47,386
It's got blue things on it.

13
00:00:47,430 --> 00:00:49,194
They're flowers,
and I didn't ask

14
00:00:49,231 --> 00:00:50,442
for the one with flowers, did I?

15
00:00:50,466 --> 00:00:51,695
No, you didn't.

16
00:00:51,734 --> 00:00:54,101
I only picked that
one up to annoy you.

17
00:00:55,871 --> 00:00:56,930
What?

18
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:58,236
You're only here three days,

19
00:00:58,274 --> 00:00:59,674
you gonna play
charades every night?

20
00:00:59,709 --> 00:01:00,709
This one?

21
00:01:00,743 --> 00:01:02,712
- Is it blue?
- Bluish, I suppose.

22
00:01:08,818 --> 00:01:10,286
And I forgot to scrape the mold

23
00:01:10,319 --> 00:01:12,379
off the cheddar this
morning, so remind chef.

24
00:01:12,421 --> 00:01:13,421
Right.

25
00:01:14,790 --> 00:01:16,019
And try to find time

26
00:01:16,058 --> 00:01:18,152
- To get the moosey's head up.
- Oh.

27
00:01:18,194 --> 00:01:20,663
It's been sitting there
for two weeks, Basil.

28
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:46,914
I mean, I'm on my own,

29
00:01:46,956 --> 00:01:48,200
the Germans are
arriving tomorrow...

30
00:02:03,139 --> 00:02:04,835
You just lie there
with your feet up

31
00:02:04,874 --> 00:02:06,137
and I'll carry you up

32
00:02:06,175 --> 00:02:08,167
another hundredweight
of lime creams.

33
00:02:14,350 --> 00:02:15,545
Still growing in,

34
00:02:15,584 --> 00:02:17,644
still burrowing its
way down to the bone,

35
00:02:17,687 --> 00:02:19,622
still macheteing its
way through the nerve?

36
00:03:48,644 --> 00:03:52,308
Yes, it is a very
simple operation,

37
00:03:52,348 --> 00:03:54,146
but it will be quite
painful afterwards.

38
00:04:12,968 --> 00:04:15,301
Evening, Fawlty. Hampshire won.

39
00:04:20,976 --> 00:04:21,944
My wife?

40
00:04:21,977 --> 00:04:22,945
That's it.

41
00:04:24,613 --> 00:04:25,991
They're taking it out
tomorrow morning.

42
00:04:26,015 --> 00:04:27,244
Is she? Good.

43
00:04:27,283 --> 00:04:28,251
Not her, the nail.

44
00:04:28,284 --> 00:04:29,843
They won't have
operated till tomorrow.

45
00:04:29,885 --> 00:04:30,978
- What?
- The nail.

46
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:32,130
They're taking it out tomorrow.

47
00:04:32,154 --> 00:04:34,714
How did she get a nail in her?

48
00:08:55,584 --> 00:08:57,246
You called, sir?

49
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:59,255
Last week. But not to worry.

50
00:08:59,288 --> 00:09:00,298
¿Qué?

51
00:09:01,423 --> 00:09:03,688
Look, go and get me a hammer.

52
00:09:03,725 --> 00:09:04,818
¿Cómo?

53
00:09:06,228 --> 00:09:08,561
"Hammer"... Oh, hammer sandwich!

54
00:09:12,367 --> 00:09:13,960
My hamster?

55
00:09:14,002 --> 00:09:15,265
No, not your hamster.

56
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:17,170
How can I knock a nail
in with your hamster?

57
00:09:17,206 --> 00:09:19,004
Well, I could try,
no, it doesn't matter,

58
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:20,518
all right, I'll get
it, you come here,

59
00:09:20,542 --> 00:09:22,135
and tidy. You know, tidy?

60
00:09:23,712 --> 00:09:26,272
I get hhhammer and hhhit you
on the hhhead with it hhhard.

61
00:18:13,677 --> 00:18:15,137
["Jealous Heart" by Al Morgan]

62
00:18:15,137 --> 00:18:19,266
<i>♪ Jealous heart
Oh, jealous heart ♪</i>

63
00:18:19,266 --> 00:18:20,809
<i>♪ Stop beating ♪</i>

64
00:18:22,519 --> 00:18:28,233
<i>♪ Can't you see the damage
You have done... ♪</i>

65
00:18:29,526 --> 00:18:34,323
[David] When he died,
he had offices in Jermyn Street.

66
00:18:45,834 --> 00:18:47,794
[woman laughs]

67
00:26:20,895 --> 00:26:22,386
and hope that your stay

68
00:26:22,430 --> 00:26:23,625
will be a happy one.

69
00:26:23,664 --> 00:26:25,792
Now, would you like to eat first

70
00:26:25,833 --> 00:26:26,833
or would you like a drink

71
00:26:26,868 --> 00:26:28,097
before the war?

72
00:26:28,136 --> 00:26:30,765
Ning... That trespassers will be

73
00:26:30,805 --> 00:26:32,774
tied up with piano wire.

74
00:26:32,807 --> 00:26:35,538
Sorry, sorry, trouble
with the old leg.

75
00:26:35,576 --> 00:26:37,568
Got a touch of
shrapnel in the war.

76
00:26:37,612 --> 00:26:40,548
Korean! Korean
war! Sorry, Korean.

77
00:26:40,581 --> 00:26:42,482
Thank you. We will eat now.

78
00:26:50,958 --> 00:26:52,503
Didn't vote for it
myself quite honestly,

79
00:26:52,527 --> 00:26:53,495
but now that we're in,

80
00:26:53,528 --> 00:26:54,671
I'm determined to make it work,

81
00:26:54,695 --> 00:26:56,173
so I'd like to welcome
you all to Britain.
